    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential NULL pointer dereference in print_fh_init() function\n\n### Summary\nThe `print_fh_init()` function in the O-RAN FHI 7.2 configuration module could crash when called with uninitialized or partially populated `xran_fh_init` structures. This occurred because the function did not properly validate pointer arguments before dereferencing them.\n\nThe issue was particularly evident when the configuration module attempted to print debug information for Ethernet addresses or string fields that were not yet initialized, causing segmentation faults in certain initialization sequences.\n\n### Changes\n- `radio/fhi_72/oran-config.c`: Added comprehensive NULL pointer checks throughout the `print_fh_init()` function and its helper functions\n- `radio/fhi_72/oran-config.c`: Added boundary checks for array indexing operations\n- `radio/fhi_72/oran-config.c`: Improved error reporting for invalid input parameters\n\n"
}